    <stitle>2 SPEED AND DOUBLE REDUCTION SINGLE DRIVE AXLES: EATON - ASSEMBLE - DRIVE PINION ( Figure 30 )</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>DRIVE PINION (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1401630">Figure 30</hotlnk>)
        </title>
        <figure id="f1401630" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1401630" filename="../figg14/G1401630.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 30. Drive Pinion Assembly - Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Lubricate parts with gear lube during reassembly. When installing bearing cones and pilot bearing,
                    use properly sized sleeves that only contact the inner bearing race.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Before installing cups, check for burrs on bearing surfaces and remove. Press bearing cups
                in cage (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401631">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401631" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401631" filename="../figg14/G1401631.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 31. Bearing Cup Installation</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press pilot bearing on pinion. Stake bearing using staking tool (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401632">Figure 32</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401633">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401632" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401632" filename="../figg14/G1401632.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 32. Pilot Bearing Installation</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1401633" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401633" filename="../figg14/G1401633.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 33. Pinion Pilot Bearing Stake Pattern</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Perform Trial Build-Up Pinion Preload Test,
                <hotlnk document="s14016_HL1401603.xml" xrefid="hl1401603">6.1.</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
